<reference id="reference_B602C82274A1400CAD96F8F87548C457">
  <title>Managing Segments Prior to Upgrading</title>
  <shortdesc> Custom segments and global access to shared segments. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Reports and analytics" />
      <othermeta name="subtopic" content="Upgrading from V14" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <refsyn id="refsyn_8E21284AD4AC432E9C778E4691DA686C">
      <p>Before upgrading to SiteCatalyst 15, Adobe recommends auditing all
		  segments that are shared by Discover users, and selecting which segments should
		  appear in the SiteCatalyst segments list. Any segments that should not be
		  shared with all SiteCatalyst users should be moved to a non-shared folder.
		  Shared segments might need to be renamed since they are visible to all
		  SiteCatalyst users. For example, you might prefix global segments with CORP: or
		  GLOBAL:, and personal segments with your name. 
		</p>
      <note>You cannot apply segments to a legacy dashboard. 
		</note>
